#
# salt[0:20] == deployer, so these stay front-run-proof even though this file is public: only that deployer
# can consume them. (The older Random-path sets in this directory are NOT deployer-bound — anyone reading
# them can squat the address, so do not reuse the free ones there.)
#
# The round-1 permissioned set is fully CONSUMED by the live suite; CREATE3 salts are single-use per
# deployer/chain. Note the address is f(deployer, salt) and NOT a function of initcode, so contract or guest
# changes do not invalidate these — only use does.
#
# Every entry verified 2026-07-23: deployer-bound, 5 leading zero bytes counted from the address itself,
# and unused on mainnet (eth_getCode empty).
